Arizona Western College ( also AWC ) is a public community college located in Yuma , Arizona . The school 's sports teams are called the Matadors and the school colors are cardinal and gold . They participate in the NJCAA , the ACCAC , and the WSFL . Arizona Western College offers approximately 98 academic programs leading to the granting of an occupational certificate or the A.A. , A.Bus. , A.S. , A.G.S. , or A.A.S. degrees . The Arizona Western College Matadors field 7 intercollegiate teams , four for men and three for women . Men 's sports at Arizona Western include baseball , football , basketball , and soccer . The Matador women compete in basketball , softball , and volleyball . Bengie Molina played shortstop for the baseball team in 1991 and 1992 . 